{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-06-24T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Zoom in on the small transaction that keeps landscapes alive: a butterfly on a yellow flower, sipping nectar. While it feeds, pollen dusts its body and hitches a ride to the next bloom—one of the quiet ways flowering plants reproduce. Pollinators are not only bees. Butterflies, birds, bats, beetles and many others help move pollen, supporting wild plants and many of the fruits and vegetables we eat.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BFPollin_EN-IN2234226266_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BFPollin_EN-IN2234226266_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Pollen meets wings","Title":"Butterfly pollinating on yellow flower","Copyright":"© lzh/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Pollinators are responsible for about one out of three bites of food we eat.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260624_BFPollin\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Pollinator+Week&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260623_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260624_BFPollin"},"Ssd":"20260624","Name":"BFPollin","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2234226266","FullDateString":"24 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Mount Fuji, Japan's highest mountain, rises to 3,776 metres on Honshu Island, about 100 kilometres southwest of Tokyo. Its near-perfect cone is a volcano—dormant since its last eruption in December 1707 yet still classed as active. That last major event is known as the Hōei eruption. It blasted ash and other tephra across eastern Japan, reaching Edo (today's Tokyo). Beyond geology, Fuji has long been treated as a sacred landscape and a destination for pilgrimage climbs, reflecting how nature, religion and daily life overlap in Japan. That enduring cultural appeal is one reason it was designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2013 as 'a sacred place and source of artistic inspiration.' Fuji is famously visible from far away on clear days but never guaranteed—clouds can hide it in minutes. Whether you hike it or just catch a glimpse from a train window, it still feels like Japan's signature on the horizon.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Fujisan_EN-IN2234581475_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Fujisan_EN-IN2234581475_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Signature on the horizon","Title":"Mount Fuji on Honshu Island, Japan","Copyright":"© phutthiseth thongtae/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.365403,138.730373/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.365403,138.730373;S9;Mount Fuji on Honshu Island, Japan&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260623_Fujisan\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mount+Fuji&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260622_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260623_Fujisan"},"Ssd":"20260623","Name":"Fujisan","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2234581475","FullDateString":"23 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"22 June is World Rainforest Day, a global moment and a year-round call to protect the world's remaining rainforests. These ecosystems aren't just dots on the map. They thrive across the tropics and beyond yet cover only about 6% of Earth's surface. Think of the Amazon in South America, the Congo Basin in Africa and the forests of Southeast Asia.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.QuinaultFerns_EN-IN6306076955_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.QuinaultFerns_EN-IN6306076955_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A lush kingdom","Title":"Quinault rainforest, Olympic National Park, Washington state, United States","Copyright":"© Chris Moore/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Rainforests are home to more than half of the world's species, despite covering only 6% of the Earth's surface.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260622_QuinaultFerns\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Rainforest+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260621_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260622_QuinaultFerns"},"Ssd":"20260622","Name":"QuinaultFerns","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"6306076955","FullDateString":"22 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At sunrise, parks around the world become giant stretching sessions as mats roll out and millions practice balance, breathing and poses that sometimes wobble more than they flow smoothly. That is the spirit of the International Day of Yoga, celebrated every year on 21 June.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.InternationalDayOfYoga2026_EN-IN8379810108_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.InternationalDayOfYoga2026_EN-IN8379810108_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Beneath the solstice sun","Title":"Colourful sky and clouds reflecting over the Ganges River, Rishikesh","Copyright":"© fbxx/iStock/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/30.1077,78.287804/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=30.1077,78.287804;S9;Rishikesh, Uttarakhand&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260621_InternationalDayOfYoga2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Day+of+Yoga&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260620_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260621_InternationalDayOfYoga2026"},"Ssd":"20260621","Name":"InternationalDayOfYoga2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"8379810108","FullDateString":"21 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A sculpted arch of ice rises from the Southern Ocean along the Antarctic Peninsula, one of the fastest-warming regions on Earth. This formation began as compacted snow that turned into glacial ice over thousands of years. Eventually, part of a glacier or floating ice shelf fractured and broke free—a process known as calving—creating a drifting iceberg.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArchedIceberg_EN-IN0531378206_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArchedIceberg_EN-IN0531378206_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"An ocean's frozen cathedral","Title":"Arched iceberg floating off the western Antarctic Peninsula, Southern Ocean","Copyright":"© Steven Kazlowski/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-69.5,-65/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-69.5,-65;S9;Antarctic Peninsula&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260620_ArchedIceberg\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Iceberg&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260619_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260620_ArchedIceberg"},"Ssd":"20260620","Name":"ArchedIceberg","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0531378206","FullDateString":"20 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Perched at the far edge of Piazza Bovio in Piombino, Tuscany, Italy, is the Piombino Lighthouse. Locally, it is known as 'Faro di Piombino' or 'La Rocchetta Lighthouse.' It overlooks the point where the Tuscan coast faces the island of Elba.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.IsolaElba_EN-IN7931152562_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.IsolaElba_EN-IN7931152562_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"What stands at the edge?","Title":"La Rocchetta Lighthouse, Piombino, Tuscany, Italy","Copyright":"© StevanZZ/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.936254,10.54206/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.936254,10.54206;S9;Lighthouse la Rocchetta, Piombino, Tuscany, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260619_IsolaElba\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lighthouse+la+Rocchetta+Piombino&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260618_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260619_IsolaElba"},"Ssd":"20260619","Name":"IsolaElba","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"7931152562","FullDateString":"19 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Set high above Cusco in Peru, Sacsayhuamán reveals the ambition of the Inca Empire in stone. Built in the 15th century, this vast complex once formed part of the sacred capital of the Incas. From above, the layout becomes clear: terraces, open plazas and the remains of towers forming a carefully planned citadel. The largest walls, built from enormous blocks, still stand strong today. Some stones rise more than 8 metres tall and were fitted together so precisely—without mortar—that the structure has endured centuries of earthquakes.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Saqsaywaman_EN-IN9988887646_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Saqsaywaman_EN-IN9988887646_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A rock-solid marvel","Title":"Aerial view of the ruins of Sacsayhuamán, Cusco, Peru","Copyright":"© Creative-Family/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-13.50778,-71.98222/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-13.50778,-71.98222;S9;Sacsayhuamán, Cusco, Peru&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260618_Saqsaywaman\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sacsayhuaman+Cusco+Peru&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260617_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260618_Saqsaywaman"},"Ssd":"20260618","Name":"Saqsaywaman","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"9988887646","FullDateString":"18 Jun, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Most rivers spend their lives flowing around obstacles. The Sharavathi River reaches the edge of a cliff and simply jumps. At Jog Falls in Karnataka, the river plunges 253 metres, making it the third-highest waterfall in India.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.JogFalls2026_EN-IN2533705121_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.JogFalls2026_EN-IN2533705121_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The art of taking the plunge","Title":"Jog Falls on the Sharavathi River, Shivamogga district, Karnataka","Copyright":"© Amith Nag Photography/Moment/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/14.228129,74.810677/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=14.228129,74.810677;S9;Jog Falls, Karnataka&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260701_JogFalls2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Jog+Falls&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260630_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260701_JogFalls2026"},"Ssd":"20260701","Name":"JogFalls2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2533705121","FullDateString":"1 Jul, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As the sun sinks low in the Masai Mara National Reserve, the silhouettes of Masai giraffes rise against a blazing sky and open plains. Another day comes to an end in the reserve, which stretches across about 1,500 square kilometres in southwestern Kenya, bordering Tanzania's Serengeti National Park. It is a vast expanse, one of the world's greatest wildlife arenas. Rolling grasslands, scattered acacia trees and the life-giving Mara River set the stage for unforgettable encounters.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_EN-IN0088128873_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_EN-IN0088128873_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where shadows stretch tall","Title":"Giraffes at sunset in the Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© danm/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-1.529493,35.170876/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-1.529493,35.170876;S9;Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Masai+Mara+National+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260629_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe"},"Ssd":"20260630","Name":"MasaiGiraffe","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0088128873","FullDateString":"30 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Observed each 29 June, the International Day of the Tropics spotlights a vast region stretching between the Tropics of Cancer and Capricorn, where warmth and rainfall shape daily life. This zone covers about 40% of Earth's surface area, yet supports around 80% of global biodiversity, making it central to planetary health and culture.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_EN-IN9424063973_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_EN-IN9424063973_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Born on fire, held by water","Title":"Bora Bora and its lagoon, South Pacific, French Polynesia","Copyright":"© Frederick Millett/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-16.498926,-151.73819/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-16.498926,-151.73819;S9;Bora Bora, French Polynesia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Day+of+the+Tropics&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260628_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon"},"Ssd":"20260629","Name":"BoraBoraLagoon","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"9424063973","FullDateString":"29 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"'Stick around' takes on a new meaning in the Sonoran Desert, where the saguaro cactus has mastered survival. With trunks and arms raised in all directions, this giant has become the American Southwest's mascot.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_EN-IN9141839272_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_EN-IN9141839272_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Looking sharp","Title":"Saguaro cacti near Windgate Pass, McDowell Range, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Eric Mischke/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/33.796104,-111.810696/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=33.796104,-111.810696;S9;Windgate Pass, McDowell Range, Arizona, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Saguaro+cactus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260627_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun"},"Ssd":"20260628","Name":"SaguaroSun","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"9141839272","FullDateString":"28 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At Boneyard Beach within Hunting Island State Park, South Carolina, United States, the first thing you notice is the trees. Then comes the question: why are bleached trunks and exposed roots scattered across the sand like a scene paused midway through collapse? Since the 1980s, Hunting Island has experienced major beach erosion, with some of the highest rates along the US East Coast—reaching up to 9 metres per year in certain areas.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_EN-IN2656634065_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_EN-IN2656634065_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The trees that lost ground","Title":"Driftwood on Boneyard Beach, Hunting Island, South Carolina, United States","Copyright":"© Frances/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/32.40758,-80.445631/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=32.40758,-80.445631;S9;Hunting Island State Park, South Carolina, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hunting+Island&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260626_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach"},"Ssd":"20260627","Name":"BoneyardBeach","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2656634065","FullDateString":"27 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What does a parliament, a clock tower and a giant wheel have in common? They all stand beside the River Thames as if London had carefully staged its icons for dramatic effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_EN-IN8289570374_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_EN-IN8289570374_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Current affairs","Title":"The River Thames, London, England","Copyright":"© Daniel Lange/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/51.50382,-0.121258/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=51.50382,-0.121258;S9;The River Thames, London, Greater London, England&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=River+Thames&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260625_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer"},"Ssd":"20260626","Name":"ThamesSummer","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"8289570374","FullDateString":"26 Jun, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Few squares in Belgium wear history as well as the Grand Place. The surrounding buildings, seen here, began as guild houses, each funded by a specific trade. Brewers, bakers, merchants and craftsmen treated architecture as language, translating work, status and rivalry into stone through reliefs, coats of arms and generous gold leaf. Styles meet without caution. Gothic verticals rise beside Baroque curves, while the Town Hall, older than its neighbours and unapologetically asymmetrical, holds the composition together.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_EN-IN3033098257_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_EN-IN3033098257_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Square up to history","Title":"Buildings on Grand-Place Square in Brussels, Belgium","Copyright":"© Vladislav Zolotov/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/50.846851,4.352454/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=50.846851,4.352454;S9;Grand-Place Square, Brussels, Belgium&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grand+Place+Brussels&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260624_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace"},"Ssd":"20260625","Name":"GrandPlace","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"303